The paper presents an algorithm for solving symmetric diagonally dominant (SDD) systems, which is a problem in numerical linear algebra. Therefore, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a likely sub-category. The algorithm involves sparsification of graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The algorithm also uses Chebyshev iteration, which is a method commonly used in numerical linear algebra, and can be considered a machine learning method, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) possible sub-categories as well. Finally, the algorithm involves graph sparsification, which is a topic in computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible sub-category.
